linux redhat:

mudar o hostname | hostnamectl set-hostname luxsrv.enta.pt

mudar para root | sudo su - 

update no sistema |  sudo yum update

reiniciar a maquina | reboot

diz onde estou | pwd

sair | exit

ir para o diretorio | cd

mostrar que ficheiros tem no diretorio | ls

criar uma pasta | mkdir

remover | rmdir

mover | mv

nano | criar um ficheiro

df | encontrar o meu disco

free | ver a memoria

find | encontrar 

?? | nao importa


VI(criar um ficheiro):

R - ler
W - escrever
x - executar 



-------------Instalar um servidor web-------------

sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 -keyout /etc/ssl/private/nginx-selfsigned.key -out /etc/ssl/certs/nginx-selfsigned.crt

ssl_certificate "/etc/pki/nginx/server.crt";
        ssl_certificate_key "/etc/pki/nginx/private/server.key";
        
        
-----------instalar o cliente linux -----------------


➡️ sudo amazon-linux-extras install epel

➡️ yum groupinstall "MATE Desktop"

➡️ sudo yum install xrdp chromium

➡️ systemctl enable --now xrdp

This will make all users to have the graphic interface
➡️ sudo bash -c 'echo PREFERRED=/usr/bin/mate-session > /etc/sysconfig/desktop'

Exit the root
This will make only a specific user to have the graphic interface
➡️ adduser user

➡️ passwd user

➡️ login user

➡️ echo "/usr/bin/mate-session" > ~/.Xclients && chmod +x ~/.Xclients


Centos 7 automatically enables FirewallD which will block port 3389 after the first reboot, therefore blocking RDP access. To fix that, open port 3389 on FirewallD as shown here:
https://serverspace.io/support/help/installing-and-configuring-an-rdp-server-on-centos-7/

$ sudo firewall-cmd --add-port=3389/tcp --permanent
$ sudo firewall-cmd --reload


